# FixHub Functional E2E — HTTP tests (VSCode REST Client)
# Base URL: API v1. Run requests in order; copy tokens/ids from responses into variables below.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5100/api/v1
@customer_token =
@technician_token =
@admin_token =
@job_id =
@proposal_id =
@customer_id =
@technician_id =
@admin_id =
@technician_b_id =

###############################################################################
# SETUP — Run once: register users and login to get tokens. Copy from responses:
# - customer_token, customer_id from Login Customer
# - technician_token, technician_id from Login Technician  
# - admin_token, admin_id from Login Admin
# Then approve technician: PATCH admin/technicians/{{technician_id}}/status with {"status": 2}
###############################################################################

### Register Customer (Setup)
### Request: POST register with role Customer
### Expected: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Cliente E2E Test",
  "email": "cliente-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "role": 1,
  "phone": "+34000000001"
}

###

### Login Customer
### Request: POST login to get JWT
### Expected: 200 — copy "token" and "userId" from response to @customer_token and @customer_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "cliente-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

###

### Register Technician (Setup)
### Request: POST register with role Technician
### Expected: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Técnico E2E Test",
  "email": "tecnico-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "role": 2,
  "phone": "+34000000002"
}

###

### Login Technician
### Request: POST login
### Expected: 200 — copy "token" and "userId" to @technician_token and @technician_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tecnico-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

###

### Register Admin (Setup)
### Request: POST register with role Admin
### Expected: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Admin E2E Test",
  "email": "admin-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "role": 3,
  "phone": null
}

###

### Login Admin
### Request: POST login
### Expected: 200 — copy "token" and "userId" to @admin_token and @admin_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

###

### Approve Technician (Setup) — required so Admin can accept proposals
### Request: PATCH technician status to Approved (2)
### Expected: 204
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/technicians/{{technician_id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": 2
}

###

###############################################################################
### SCENARIO_1_NORMAL_FLOW
### Flujo completo: Crear job → Propuesta → Admin acepta → Técnico inicia → Cliente completa
###############################################################################

### 1.1 Create Job (Customer)
### Request: POST create job as customer
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" from response to @job_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "Reparación E2E flujo normal",
  "description": "Descripción del trabajo",
  "addressText": "Calle Test 1",
  "lat": null,
  "lng": null,
  "budgetMin": 50,
  "budgetMax": 150
}

###

### 1.2 Technician sends proposal
### Request: POST submit proposal for job
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" from response to @proposal_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{technician_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 100,
  "message": "Puedo ir mañana"
}

###

### 1.3 Admin accepts proposal
### Request: POST accept proposal (creates JobAssignment)
### Expected: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/proposals/{{proposal_id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.4 Technician starts job
### Request: POST start job (Assigned → InProgress)
### Expected: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{technician_token}}

###

### 1.5 Customer completes job
### Request: POST complete job
### Expected: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###

### 1.6 Get job (verify final state)
### Request: GET job by id
### Expected: 200 — status should be "Completed"
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###

###############################################################################
### SCENARIO_2_CANCEL_BEFORE_ASSIGN
### Cliente crea job y cancela antes de que se asigne técnico
###############################################################################

### 2.1 Create Job (Customer)
### Request: POST create job
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" to @job_id for next steps
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "Job a cancelar antes de asignación",
  "description": "Descripción",
  "addressText": "Calle Test 2",
  "lat": null,
  "lng": null,
  "budgetMin": 30,
  "budgetMax": 80
}

###

### 2.2 Customer cancels job (before any proposal accepted)
### Request: POST cancel job
### Expected: 200 — status "Cancelled", cancelledAt present
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###

### 2.3 Get job (verify cancelled)
### Request: GET job
### Expected: 200 — status "Cancelled"
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###

###############################################################################
### SCENARIO_3_CANCEL_AFTER_ASSIGN
### Job asignado; cliente cancela después de que Admin acepta propuesta
###############################################################################

### 3.1 Create Job (Customer)
### Request: POST create job
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" to @job_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "Job a cancelar después de asignación",
  "description": "Descripción",
  "addressText": "Calle Test 3",
  "lat": null,
  "lng": null,
  "budgetMin": 40,
  "budgetMax": 90
}

###

### 3.2 Technician sends proposal
### Request: POST proposal
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" to @proposal_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{technician_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 60,
  "message": "Propuesta para escenario 3"
}

###

### 3.3 Admin accepts proposal
### Request: POST accept proposal
### Expected: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/proposals/{{proposal_id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

### 3.4 Customer cancels job (after assignment)
### Request: POST cancel job
### Expected: 200 — status "Cancelled"
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###

### 3.5 Get job (verify cancelled)
### Request: GET job
### Expected: 200 — status "Cancelled"
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###

###############################################################################
### SCENARIO_4_ADMIN_REASSIGN
### Job asignado a Técnico A; Admin reasigna a Técnico B (need second technician)
### Setup: Register a second technician, approve, set @technician_b_id. Use same job.
###############################################################################

### 4.1 Register second technician (Setup for scenario 4)
### Request: POST register Technician B
### Expected: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Técnico B E2E",
  "email": "tecnico-b-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "role": 2,
  "phone": "+34000000003"
}

###

### 4.2 Login Technician B — copy "userId" to @technician_b_id
### Request: POST login
### Expected: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tecnico-b-e2e@test.fixhub",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

###

### 4.3 Approve Technician B
### Request: PATCH status Approved
### Expected: 204
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/technicians/{{technician_b_id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": 2
}

###

### 4.4 Create Job (Customer)
### Request: POST create job
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" to @job_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "Job para reasignación",
  "description": "Descripción",
  "addressText": "Calle Test 4",
  "lat": null,
  "lng": null,
  "budgetMin": 50,
  "budgetMax": 120
}

###

### 4.5 Technician A sends proposal
### Request: POST proposal
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" to @proposal_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{technician_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 80,
  "message": "Técnico A"
}

###

### 4.6 Admin accepts proposal (assigns to Technician A)
### Request: POST accept proposal
### Expected: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/proposals/{{proposal_id}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

### 4.7 Admin reassigns job to Technician B
### Request: POST reassign to technician_b_id
### Expected: 200 — jobId, newAssignmentId, toTechnicianId, overrideId
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/jobs/{{job_id}}/reassign
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toTechnicianId": "{{technician_b_id}}",
  "reason": "Reasignación E2E por disponibilidad",
  "reasonDetail": "Detalle opcional"
}

###

### 4.8 Get job (verify still Assigned, technician should be B)
### Request: GET job
### Expected: 200 — status "Assigned", assignedTechnicianId = technician_b_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

###############################################################################
### SCENARIO_5_SUSPENDED_CUSTOMER
### Admin suspende cliente; cliente intenta crear job (puede 201 o 403 según política)
###############################################################################

### 5.1 Admin suspends customer
### Request: POST suspend user (customer_id)
### Expected: 204
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/{{customer_id}}/suspend
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "suspendedUntil": null,
  "suspensionReason": "Prueba E2E suspensión cliente"
}

###

### 5.2 Customer tries to create job (may succeed 201 if no check, or 403 if blocked)
### Request: POST create job as suspended customer
### Expected: 201 (current behaviour) or 403 (if product blocks suspended users)
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "Job intento cliente suspendido",
  "description": "Descripción",
  "addressText": "Calle Test 5",
  "lat": null,
  "lng": null,
  "budgetMin": 20,
  "budgetMax": 50
}

###

### 5.3 Admin unsuspends customer (cleanup for other scenarios)
### Request: POST unsuspend user
### Expected: 204
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/{{customer_id}}/unsuspend
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

###############################################################################
### SCENARIO_6_SUSPENDED_TECHNICIAN
### Admin suspende técnico; técnico intenta enviar propuesta o iniciar job
###############################################################################

### 6.1 Create Job (Customer) — for technician to propose/start
### Request: POST create job
### Expected: 201 — copy "id" to @job_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "Job para técnico suspendido",
  "description": "Descripción",
  "addressText": "Calle Test 6",
  "lat": null,
  "lng": null,
  "budgetMin": 35,
  "budgetMax": 70
}

###

### 6.2 Admin suspends technician
### Request: POST suspend technician
### Expected: 204
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/{{technician_id}}/suspend
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "suspendedUntil": null,
  "suspensionReason": "Prueba E2E suspensión técnico"
}

###

### 6.3 Suspended technician tries to send proposal (may 201 or 403)
### Request: POST submit proposal
### Expected: 201 (current) or 403 (if product blocks suspended)
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{technician_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 50,
  "message": "Propuesta desde técnico suspendido"
}

###

### 6.4 Admin unsuspends technician (cleanup)
### Request: POST unsuspend
### Expected: 204
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/{{technician_id}}/unsuspend
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

###############################################################################
# Optional: Get job proposals (Admin or Customer owner)
###############################################################################

### Get proposals for a job
### Request: GET proposals for job_id
### Expected: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{job_id}}/proposals
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

### List customer's jobs (mine)
### Request: GET jobs/mine
### Expected: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/mine
Authorization: Bearer {{customer_token}}

###
